questiontext.text:
Here is a cumulative frequency diagram of the time spent reading by a class of students over a particular evening.
You may move the pink lines by dragging the points along the axes.


[[jsxgraph width="600px" height="750px"]] // Coordinates of points on diagram var coordList = [ {#p1#}, {#p2#}, {#p3#}, {#p4#}, {#p5#}, {#p6#} ]; JXG.Options.text.useMathJax=true; var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, { boundingBox:[-5,55,45,-5], showCopyright:false, showNavigation:false, keepAspectRatio:false, grid:true }); // Defining axes var yAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [0,50]], { highlight:false, name:"\\(cf\\)", withLabel:true, label:{ fixed:true, highlight:false, position:"rt", offset:[-15,-15], anchorX:"right", fontSize:15, useMathJax:true, parse:false }, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"right", offset:[-10,0] } } }); var xAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [40,0]], { highlight:false, name:"\\(t \\ [min]\\)", withLabel:true, label:{ fixed:true, highlight:false, position:"rt", offset:[-5,-35], anchorX:"right", fontSize:15, useMathJax:true, parse:false }, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"middle", offset:[0,-15] } } }); // Drawing diagram var i; var segList = []; for (i in coordList) { board.create("point", coordList[i], { fixed:true, highlight:false, showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); if (i > 0) { segList.push(board.create("segment", [coordList[i], coordList[i-1]], { fixed:true, highlight:false, })); }; }; // Creating user interactive lines var yAxisSegment = board.create("segment", [[0,0], [0,coordList[5][1]]], { fixed:true, visible:false }); var yGlider = board.create("glider", [0, 50, yAxisSegment], { fillColor:"#F757FF", strokeColor:"#F757FF", showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); var yLine = board.create("line", [ yGlider, function(){return [yGlider.X()+1, yGlider.Y()]} ], { highlight:false, strokeColor:"#F757FF", strokeWidth:2, dash:1 }); var xAxisSegment = board.create("segment", [[coordList[0][0],0], [coordList[5][0],0]], { fixed:true, visible:false }); var xGlider = board.create("glider", [40, 0, xAxisSegment], { fillColor:"#F757FF", strokeColor:"#F757FF", showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); var xLine = board.create("line", [ xGlider, function(){return [xGlider.X(), xGlider.Y()+1]} ], { highlight:false, strokeColor:"#F757FF", strokeWidth:2, dash:1 }); [[/jsxgraph]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked solution

\(a\):

The values of cumulative frequency can be read off the \(y\) axis of the graph:


[[jsxgraph width="400px" height="500px"]] // Coordinates of points on diagram var coordList = [ {#p1#}, {#p2#}, {#p3#}, {#p4#}, {#p5#}, {#p6#} ]; JXG.Options.text.useMathJax=true; var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, { boundingBox:[-5,55,45,-5], showCopyright:false, showNavigation:false, keepAspectRatio:false, grid:true }); // Defining axes var yAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [0,50]], { highlight:false, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"right", offset:[-10,0] } } }); var xAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [40,0]], { highlight:false, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"middle", offset:[0,-15] } } }); // Drawing diagram var i; var segList = []; for (i in coordList) { board.create("point", coordList[i], { fixed:true, highlight:false, showInfoBox:false, size:2, withLabel:false }); if (i > 0) { segList.push(board.create("segment", [coordList[i], coordList[i-1]], { fixed:true, highlight:false, })); }; }; // Creating lines console.log(coordList); for (i in coordList.slice(1)) { board.create("line", [ coordList.slice(1)[i], function(){return [coordList.slice(1)[i][0]+1, coordList.slice(1,)[i][1]]} ], { highlight:false, strokeColor:"red", strokeWidth:2, dash:1 }); }; [[/jsxgraph]]


You can then find the frequency of each range by the difference between consecutive cumulative frequencies.


Range Frequency Cumulative Frequency
\(0 < t \leq {@first(p1)@}\) \(0\) \(0\)
\({@first(p1)@} < t \leq {@first(p2)@}\) \({@second(p2)-second(p1)@} \ \ (= {@second(p2)@} - {@second(p1)@})\) \({@second(p2)@}\)
\({@first(p2)@} < t \leq {@first(p3)@}\) \({@second(p3)-second(p2)@} \ \ (= {@second(p3)@} - {@second(p2)@})\) \({@second(p3)@}\)
\({@first(p3)@} < t \leq {@first(p4)@}\) \({@second(p4)-second(p3)@} \ \ (= {@second(p4)@} - {@second(p3)@})\) \({@second(p4)@}\)
\({@first(p4)@} < t \leq {@first(p5)@}\) \({@second(p5)-second(p4)@} \ \ (= {@second(p5)@} - {@second(p4)@})\) \({@second(p5)@}\)
\({@first(p5)@} < t \leq {@first(p6)@}\) \({@second(p6)-second(p5)@} \ \ (= {@second(p6)@} - {@second(p5)@})\) \({@second(p6)@}\)



\(b\)

Since there are \({@second(p6)@}\) pieces of data, the median value can be estimated from the \(\frac{{@second(p6)@}}{2} = {@if integerp(second(p6)/2) then second(p6)/2 else float(second(p6)/2)@}\) piece of data.

Reading across from \({@if integerp(second(p6)/2) then second(p6)/2 else float(second(p6))@}\) on the \(y\) axis will give the median value on the \(x\) axis:


[[jsxgraph width="400px" height="500px"]] // Coordinates of points on diagram var coordList = [ {#p1#}, {#p2#}, {#p3#}, {#p4#}, {#p5#}, {#p6#} ]; JXG.Options.text.useMathJax=true; var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, { boundingBox:[-5,55,45,-5], showCopyright:false, showNavigation:false, keepAspectRatio:false, grid:true }); // Defining axes var yAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [0,50]], { highlight:false, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"right", offset:[-10,0] } } }); var xAxis = board.create("axis", [[0,0], [40,0]], { highlight:false, ticks:{ label:{ highlight:false, anchorX:"middle", offset:[0,-15] } } }); // Drawing diagram var i; var segList = []; for (i in coordList) { board.create("point", coordList[i], { fixed:true, highlight:false, showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); if (i > 0) { segList.push(board.create("segment", [coordList[i], coordList[i-1]], { fixed:true, highlight:false, })); }; }; // Creating user interactive lines var yAxisSegment = board.create("segment", [[0,0], [0,coordList[5][1]]], { fixed:true, visible:false }); var yGlider = board.create("glider", [0, {#second(p6)/2#}, yAxisSegment], { fixed:true, highlight:false, fillColor:"#F757FF", strokeColor:"#F757FF", showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); var yLine = board.create("line", [ yGlider, function(){return [yGlider.X()+1, yGlider.Y()]} ], { fixed:true, highlight:false, strokeColor:"#F757FF", strokeWidth:2, dash:1 }); var xAxisSegment = board.create("segment", [[coordList[0][0],0], [coordList[5][0],0]], { fixed:true, visible:false }); var xGlider = board.create("glider", [{#med#}, 0, xAxisSegment], { fixed:true, highlight:false, fillColor:"#F757FF", strokeColor:"#F757FF", showInfoBox:false, size:3, withLabel:false }); var xLine = board.create("line", [ xGlider, function(){return [xGlider.X(), xGlider.Y()+1]} ], { fixed:true, highlight:false, strokeColor:"#F757FF", strokeWidth:2, dash:1 }); [[/jsxgraph]]


Reading off the \(x\) axis, the median value of the data is: \({@if integerp(med) then med else if integerp(10*med) then float(round_prop(10*med)/10) else float(round_prop(100*med)/100)@} = {@round_prop(med)@}\) (to the nearest whole unit)


For the Lower Quartile:
Reading off \(\frac{{@second(p6)@}}{4} = {@if integerp(second(p6)/4) then second(p6)/4 else float(second(p6)/4)@}\) from the \(y\) axis gives \({@if integerp(LQ) then LQ else if integerp(10*LQ) then float(round_prop(10*LQ)/10) else float(round_prop(100*LQ)/100)@} = {@round_prop(LQ)@}\) (to the nearest whole unit)


For the Upper Quartile:
Reading off \(\frac{3 \times {@second(p6)@}}{4} = {@if integerp(3*second(p6)/4) then 3*second(p6)/4 else float(3*second(p6)/4)@}\) from the \(y\) axis gives \({@if integerp(UQ) then UQ else if integerp(10*UQ) then float(round_prop(10*UQ)/10) else float(round_prop(100*UQ)/100)@} = {@round_prop(UQ)@}\) (to the nearest whole unit)
